import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    for source in data['source'].unique():
        source_data = data[data['source'] == source]
        ax.plot(source_data['year'], source_data['net_generation'], label=source)
    
    ax.set_title('What is the trend in net generation over the years?')
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Net Generation')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    
    data_pivot = data.pivot_table(index='year', columns='source', values='net_generation', aggfunc='sum')
    data_pivot.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True, figsize=(10, 6))
    
    plt.title("What is the distribution of net generation by source?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Year")
    plt.ylabel("Net Generation")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title="Source")
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data_grouped = data.groupby('source')['net_generation'].sum()
    plt.pie(data_grouped, labels=data_grouped.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title('What is the proportion of net generation from renewable sources?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title="Sources", loc="upper left")
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year

    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    scatter = ax.scatter(data['year'], data['net_generation'], c=data['source'].cat.codes, cmap='viridis')
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Net Generation')
    ax.set_title('What is the correlation between net generation and year?', wrap=True)

    legend1 = ax.legend(*scatter.legend_elements(), title="Sources")
    ax.add_artist(legend1)

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
